		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Dec 8th 3:31 PM 2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=9762393304898&num=5&post=1&replyto=9762894793995"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=9762894793995></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Well I play a dwarf warrior (they just simply rock:) because they have small armour (less weight) so you can carry more stuff in your packs. You also get a bonus on sense heading (very useful) it starts at 50. When you jump while running forward, you do this tuck and roll thing (pretty cool). Also you are small so you can move around things easier and it gives you an excellent view when standing in front of the ladies:) Butcher Block mountains is where you will start and it is one of, if not the best, newbie zone in the whole game. You will also be able to hunt at the chessboard (a chess board for the gods) Your weapon skills will go up automaticly. I am level 18 and have maxed out (for my level that is) ALL of the weapon skills. So please save yourself some headach and practice with 1hs,2hs,1hb,2hb and pierce. Also make sure to practice swimming and bandaging, you will need both later (belive me)&nbsp;&nbsp;Learn how to ghetto bash (there is info on this site here) so you can max out Bash and Kick. Your answer to what class is the Best for a warrior is a Troll. I have never played one, but they get regain (health comes back faster) and they get slam (large reaces only, Troll Ogre and Barbarian) which is pretty much like bash (you can stun things) but you do not have to have a shield to do so (so ghetto bashing is not neccessary when you are a Large race) Trolls level the slowest (that sux) and are an evil race, so it is not easy playing this race (most towns are good, and they will kill you on site(KOS) )Ogre is a large race (you get slam) and they have the best STR and AGI in the game, which is awesome but no regain:( So if you go for an Ogre or Troll make sure you pick the Troll if you are going to be on all the time (more time to lvl up) but if you are going to play here and there you may want an Ogre (note: they have some trouble moving around in dungeons because of their size). But if you decide to go for a good race, then a Dwarf is second to none:)<br><br>Magamus<br>Sarynr (forgot how to spell my server name:(<br>Master Fletcher<br>All around good guy<br>Hail Fist!<br>I AM MAGAMUS!</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
